HEADWORD: Escroll
<hw>Es*croll"</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Escrow</er>, <er>Scroll</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A scroll.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A long strip or
scroll resembling a ribbon or a band of parchment, or the like,
anciently placed above the shield, and supporting the crest.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>In modern heraldry, a similar ribbon on which the
motto is inscribed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Escrow</ent>⟦br⟧
